summary: ME: I’m glad that “Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse” is getting rave reviews and I’m hoping that the main heroes relationships...
body:
ME: I’m glad that “Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse” is getting rave reviews and I’m hoping that the main heroes relationships with one another will be handled with dignity and respect–

INTERNET: Hey, did you hear that the two creators of “Voltron” are directing the sequels?

ALSO ME: Let the squicky inter-generational fan-shipping that completely overshadows the sci-fi mythology and epic storytelling commence!!!!!

summary:
Amazing Spider-Man (Vol. 1) Annual 1997 Writer:  Roger Stern & Kurt Busiek, Pencils:  Tom Lyle

 Peter is lost in thought and MJ...
caption:
Amazing Spider-Man (Vol. 1) Annual 1997 Writer: Roger Stern & Kurt Busiek, Pencils: Tom Lyle

Peter is lost in thought and MJ asks what’s on his mind. He tries to avoid it by telling her that he was thinking about old times, but she sees right through him. Peter fesses up and says he’s worried about Sundown and he has no idea how to find the guy. MJ suggests thinking like a news hound and enlisting the aid of someone at the Bugle. Ah, what would Peter do without MJ? –SpiderFan.org
